          {
            "commit": "6fcf6581f5bd1cf4ff878b0acc8ecb59cc1a472f",
            "subject": "LU-4961 lustre: remove liblustre.h and obd.h from userspace"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "John L. Hammond",
          "email": "john.hammond@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-05-08 19:17:05.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "John L. Hammond",
          "email": "john.hammond@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-05-09 16:43:00.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-5011 lustre: don't export kernel types to userspace",
        "message": "LU-5011 lustre: don't export kernel types to userspace\n\nTHIS IS A DRAFT PATCH FOR DISCUSSION I DID NOT TRY TO FIX ALL OF\nTHE TAB ALIGNMENT OR WHITESPACE ISSUES. PLEASE DO NOT CLUTTER THE\nDISCUSSION HERE ABOUT HOW I CAN FIX THIS OR THAT HERE OR THERE.\nTHIS MEANS YOU ANDREAS!\n\nRemove libcfs/posix/posix-types.h. Add a new header libcfs/types.h\nwhich imports the fixed-width types intXX_t and uintXX_t for use in\npackaged headers like lustreapi.h and lustre_user.h and in userspace\ncomponents. Rewrite those headers to use the new types. Including\nthese headers will no longer define the __{s,u}XX types unless Lustre\nis being built. Remove the autoconf tests for the presence of\n__{s,u}XX, and for the long-longiness of the primitive type used to\ndefine __u64.\n\nSigned-off-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I0da45fca397ffbf399f4bb2579d89b21ef865f0a\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
